name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: The #COVID19 vaccine gives us an opportunity to heal - and not just physically. By coming together in a bipartisan way, Kentucky stands united and ready to build back stronger. #TogetherKY

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: The folks at @moreheadstate ring their bell every day at 10 AM in a display of #TeamKentucky strength and unity. Thank you for showing that we are in this together, @News_MSU.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: The #COVID19 vaccine is safe and is a crucial step in ending the fight against the virus. To learn more about how it was made, how it works and the different phases of distribution, call our vaccine hotline at 800-722-5725. #AShotofRelief  https://t.co/hoTTj1qLVX

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: We know there are lots of questions regarding school reopening next month. Head to @KyDeptofEd and look for the #ReopeningTip hashtag for answers and guidance. You can find more reopening info at:  https://t.co/kNTipYbLKe.  https://t.co/RhJAAzWQlE

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Every Kentuckian, no matter their zip code, has a right to get tested for #COVID19. #TeamKentucky won't stop expanding testing opportunities until this fight is over.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: With the recommended start date approaching soon, our schools are preparing to welcome students back into the classroom. But because the virus continues to spread, it's important you know the options we're offering every family. #HealthyAtSchool  https://t.co/F6MC2nPpOP

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Watch today's live update:  https://t.co/HQCYVHEJxq

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: This holiday season, my family decided to keep our lights up through Jan. 31. @frankfortreg is using this as a way to show appreciation to our health care workers - so they can see our lights when changing shifts & know they have our continued support. I hope you'll join us!  https://t.co/xoXWzlXyTH

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: In times of uncertainty, we see how a good education helps lead us to life-saving solutions. Through programs like FCCLA, our youth are being taught lifelong skills to ensure they have the tools they need to be successful in life beyond school.  https://t.co/3jaRk8AX7v

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: With #COVID19 vaccines becoming more widely available, it's important to be informed about scammers seeking to take advantage of Kentuckians. Read more:  https://t.co/ZG7hFhBRTW  https://t.co/8mfk9bpbYk

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Another Kentucky night made warmer by the glow of green lights, signifying our remembrance of those we have lost and the hope we maintain for our future. #TogetherKY  https://t.co/cPi6cIStxw

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: KDLA’s Workforce Grants help close the digital divide and give those who lack computers and home internet access the opportunity to participate. I'm thrilled for the additional access this will bring to rural Kentuckians. #TeamKentucky

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: We know there are lots of questions surrounding the COVID-19 vaccine. Our vaccine hotline is available to help. Call (800) 722-5725. 24 hours, 7 days a week.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: "It’s the best way to protect us all from this COVID virus and I am just so happy that it’s finally here.”  -Army Private First Class Norris Hardison, receiving the first vaccination of a veteran at a state veterans center, at Thomson-Hood Veterans Center. #AShotofRelief  https://t.co/Vi904pjGID

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: In spite of this year's challenges, today we are reflecting on all that we have to celebrate and be grateful for. Merry Christmas from the Coleman-O'Bryans!  https://t.co/gqgXcQFKTk

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: This Christmas Eve, I am going to bed knowing that tomorrow, one more person will be vaccinated. One more life will be saved. We are getting through this together, and that is the best gift I could ever receive. ^JC  https://t.co/6kQdlRad6U

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Keeping with the holiday spirit, I ask that you reach out to someone who might be celebrating alone this year. We can’t be present in ways that we’re used to, but there are many ways of showing you care. Happy Holidays, #TeamKentucky.  https://t.co/kxfxSNgSU8

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: This Christmas, our family asks that you join us in avoiding large gatherings. In service to those we love and in memory of those we lost, please follow our holiday guidance. #MaskUpKY  https://t.co/yvKxeHPIR6  https://t.co/eCgmFcf1lp
